      <p>Britain’s two largest leukaemia organisations, Leukaemia U.K and Leukaemia Care approached us to deliver their UK-wide campaign for Blood Cancer Awareness Month, raising awareness of the 3 key symptoms of leukaemia.</p>

      <p>With Covid symptoms ingrained on everyone’s minds, a radical advertising approach would be required to divert attention to a completely new set of serious symptoms. Brave and attention-grabbing, our campaign centred around a blue-and-gold macaw who was specially trained to create a piece of music that would make leukaemia symptoms memorable.</p>
      <p>The campaign generated 10 million impressions and provoked a 12% increase in leukaemia enquiries via the NHS.</p>

